            . I am a <rs id="t18280703-152-viclabel764" type="occupation">salesman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280703-152-victim898 t18280703-152-viclabel764"></join> and live in St. James's market. The prisoner was in my employ, and was to sell hay for me, and give me the money; he accounts to me as often as he sells any - he brings me the money, and it is my duty to book it; he sold half a load on the 8th of May, but he never brought me the money; he left the team in the street; I met him about three weeks afterwards, in the Edgware-road, and gave him in charge; he had lived with me a year or two before.</p>
